    • Method Detail

      • classLoader

        public abstract Reflection.ClassLoader classLoader()
        Returns the defining class loader of this class (i.e., the one that created and registered this class by calling ClassLoader#notifyClassLoaded(ClassNode). Note that the defining loader of a class cannot change. If this class is included in another loaded (via ClassLoader#insertClass(Class) this function continues to return the same classloader.
        Returns:
        the defining class loader of this class.

      • typeName

        public abstract java.lang.String typeName()
        Returns the type name of this class.

        For reference types, this means the fully qualified name of the class, with package elements separated by the '.' character. A type name retains the '$' character as the separator between the other and the inner class names.

        For primitive types, this means the keyword representing the type.

        For array types, this means the array component type as above, followed by a corresponding number of pair square brackets.

        Returns:
        the canonical name of this class.

      • internalName

        public abstract java.lang.String internalName()
        Returns the internal name of this class.

        For reference types, this means the fully qualified class name with package elements separated by the '/' character.

        Primitive types do not really have an internal name, but for simplicity, we just use the corresponding keyword. This differs from Type in ASM, which does not provide internal name for primitive types.

        Returns:
        the internal name of this class.
